        "header": "2MobileForge",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.19930/2606.19930v1/images/mobileforge-overview/mobileforge-overview.drawio.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:Overview ofMobileForge.",
                "position": 396
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.19930/2606.19930v1/images/mobilegym/mobilegym.drawio.png",
                "caption": "Figure 4:MobileGymas the annotation-free adaptation substrate.MobileGymgrounds adaptation in real target-app interaction: it explores reachable GUI states, mines trajectory-grounded tasks throughMobileGym-Curriculum, and evaluates completed attempts withMobileGym-Criticto produce trajectory-level outcomes, step-level process feedback, and corrective hints.",
                "position": 492
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.19930/2606.19930v1/images/hifpo/hifpo.drawio.png",
                "caption": "Figure 5:HiFPO converts hierarchical feedback into policy updates.HiFPO performs hint-guided multi-attempt rollout, removes mastered all-success tasks, retains difficult and partially solved tasks, extracts reasonable local steps from hierarchical feedback, and trains the policy with hint-contextualized step-level GRPO.",
                "position": 563
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.19930/2606.19930v1/images/case-add-hint/case-study-hint.drawio.png",
                "caption": "Figure 6:Example of corrective hints improving rollout.A failed or partial attempt can still expose useful app knowledge.MobileGym-Criticsummarizes the failure as a compact hint, and later attempts use the hint to avoid repeated mistakes and complete the task more reliably.",
                "position": 604
            }
        ]
    },
